Denison Mines, Rogers Communications: Canada Equity Preview

-- B y   J e n n i f e r   A .   J o h n s o n
-- 
2011-02-23T05:00:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/denison-mines-rogers-communications-canada-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Canadian trading.    Denison Mines Corp . (DML CN): The Toronto-based uranium
mining company said it is offering to acquire White Canyon
Uranium Ltd. for 24 Australian cents a share or about A$57
million ($56.95 million). Perth, Western Australia-based White
Canyon’s directors recommended shareholders accept the offer,
subject to an independent expert’s opinion that it is fair and
reasonable.  Rogers Communications Inc. (RCI/B CN):  Canada ’s largest
wireless carrier said it agreed to purchase 1.4 million of its
shares for about $44.9 million, or about $32.07 a share. Rogers
declined 1.4 percent to C$34.41 a share yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jennifer Johnson in New York at 
 jjohnson156@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Baker at   nbaker7@bloomberg.net . 